race.comment: EAGLE EXPRESS (6) good mare progressing quickly through the grades. Sprinted well fresh when she defeated weaker opposition over 1200m at this track in BM72 class. Shouldn't have a problem coming back to the 1100m with the fast tempo anticipated. STORMLAND (9) meets EAGLE EXPRESS better at the weights after going under narrowly from the awkward gate at Rosehill. At his top for this and no surprise to see him return to winning form at the good odds. BEV'S NINE (1) relished the heavy (8) conditions first-up when he demolished a decent field in good style over this course and distance. Undefeated in four starts and Grima's 3kg claim keeps him in contention from the sticky gate. SIGNOR TORTONI (2) returned from a let-up with a tough on-pace win over 1200m at Warwick Farm. Capable at this level and gets every chance from the soft gate. ARRIVING HOME (4) lightly raced mare returning from a lengthy break. Went quickly through the grades in her first prep and can surprise fresh.
